.TH "ubi_change_vtbl_record" 9 "ubi_change_vtbl_record" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ubi_change_vtbl_record \- change volume table record.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ubi_change_vtbl_record
.BI "(struct ubi_device *ubi "  ","
.BI "int idx "  ","
.BI "struct ubi_vtbl_record *vtbl_rec "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ubi" 12
UBI device description object
.IP "idx" 12
table index to change
.IP "vtbl_rec" 12
new volume table record
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function changes volume table record \fIidx\fP. If \fIvtbl_rec\fP is NULL, empty
volume table record is written. The caller does not have to calculate CRC of
the record as it is done by this function. Returns zero in case of success
and a negative error code in case of failure.
